               <occupation type="political"> minister </occupation>
               <occupation type="literary">writer</occupation>
               <birth when="1890"> He was born in <placeName ref="LOC1249Addisg"/> in <date>1890</date>. </birth>
               
               
               <floruit notBefore="1916" notAfter="1963">He was both an accomplished politician and writer. 
                  He received a traditional education at <placeName ref="INS0341DL"/> and 
                  was then educated at the Emperor's court. From <date>1916</date> until the time of Italian invasion, he served in various government posts. 
                  After the liberation, he embarked on a rapid career in the government. In May <date>1941</date>, he became the Minister of the Interior and Chairman of the Council of Ministers. 
                  In the following year, he was appointed a Prime Minister. In <date>1944</date>, he became the President of the Assembly established to renegotiate the agreement between 
                  <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop"/> and <placeName ref="Q145"/>. </floruit>
               
               <death when="1963"> He died in <placeName ref="LOC1216AddisA"/> in <date>1963</date>. </death>
               
